The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for enhancing the quality of encoded frames in HEVC. This involves utilizing both spatial and temporal information from multiple adjacent frames. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves developing a deep neural network, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves video compression, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
